#### `a`

~~~ .xmp.php
a($o, $safe = true);
~~~

Convert object to array:

~~~ .php
$test = new stdClass;
$test->a = 'b';
$test->c = new Date;
$test->d = (object) [
    'year' => 0,
    'month' => 0,
    'day' => 0
];

$test = a($test);
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test = [
    'a' => 'b',
    'c' => Date::__set_state([
        'date' => '2016-12-25 23:11:16'
    ]),
    'd' => [
        'year' => 0,
        'month' => 0,
        'day' => 0
    ]
];
~~~

> **Note:** Class instance will not be converted into array.

