#### `o`

~~~ .xmp.php
o($a, $safe = true);
~~~

Convert array to object:

~~~ .php
$test = o([
    'a' => 'b',
    'c' => 'd',
    'e' => ['f', 'g', 'h', 'i'],
    'j' => [
        0 => 'k',
        1 => 'l',
        '2' => 'm'
    ],
    'n' => [
        0 => 'o',
        1 => 'p',
        'q' => 'r'
    ]
]);
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test = stdClass::__set_state([
    'a' => 'b',
    'c' => 'd',
    'e' => ['f', 'g', 'h', 'i'],
    'j' => ['k', 'l', 'm'],
    'n' => stdClass::__set_state([
        0 => 'o',
        1 => 'p',
        'q' => 'r'
    ])
]);
~~~

> **Note:** Array with numeric keys will not be converted into object.

